# OpenPill Docs Consistency

- Keep docs aligned with runtime behavior:
  - New env vars must be documented with safe defaults.
  - If behavior changes, update affected docs in the same change.
- Preserve naming consistency:
  - Use "OpenPill" as product name in user-facing docs.
  - Mention legacy names only when explaining compatibility/fallback.
- For operational sections:
  - Prefer explicit copy/paste commands.
  - Mark optional steps clearly.
- For release readiness docs:
  - Keep status entries concrete (done/in-progress/blocker), not vague placeholders.
  - Reflect real validation status (tests/smokes) before changing Go/No-Go language.
- Keep docs concise and scannable:
  - Short headings, short bullets, avoid long narrative blocks.
